<headline>Flood Advisory issued June 12 at 2:54PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM MDT TUESDAY...
* WHAT...Small stream flooding caused by rain and snowmelt is
expected.
* WHERE...Portions of Madison County, including the drainage streams
of the Tobacco Root Mountains and the city of Pony.
* WHEN...Until 300 PM MDT Tuesday.
* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
Dangerous flows over low-water crossings.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 246 PM MDT, Emergency management reported flooding due to
snow melt and recent rainfall. Small stream and low land
flooding is occurring.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Pony.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood</description>
<instruction>Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
